ty (UK)#Overall leader of the Conservative Party: 1834\u20131922|Conservative Leader in the Commons]]|years=1891\u20131911}}\n{{s-aft|rows=2|after=[[Bonar Law]]}}\n{{s-bef|before=[[Robert Gascoyne-Cecil, 3rd Marquess of Salisbury|The 3rd Marquess of Salisbury]]}}\n{{s-ttl|title=[[Leaders of the Conservative Party (UK)|Leader of the British Conservative Party]]|years=1902\u20131911}}\n{{s-aca}}\n{{s-bef|before=[[Donald Mackay, 11th Lord Reay|The Lord Reay]]}}\n{{s-ttl|title=[[Rector of the University of St Andrews]]|years=1886\u20131889}}\n{{s-aft|after=[[Frederick Hamilton-Temple-Blackwood, 1st Marquess of Dufferin and Ava|The Marquess of Dufferin and Ava]]}}\n{{s-bef|before=[[Robert Bulwer-Lytton, 1st Earl of Lytton|The Earl of Lytton]]}}\n{{s-ttl|title=[[Rector of the University of Glasgow]]|years=1890\u20131893}}\n{{s-aft|after=[[John Eldon Gorst]]}}\n{{s-bef|before=[[John Inglis, Lord Glencorse|Lord Glencorse]]}}\n{{s-ttl|title=[[Chancellor of the University of Edinburgh]]|years=1891\u20131930}}\n{{s-aft|after=[[J. M. Barrie]]}}\n{{s-bef|before=[[John Strutt, 3rd Baron Rayleigh|The Lord Rayleigh]]}}\n{{s-ttl|title=[[Chancellor of the University of Cambridge]]|years=1919\u20131930}}\n{{s-aft|after=[[Stanley Baldwin]]}}\n{{S-new|institution}}\n{{s-ttl|title=Visitor of [[Girton College, Cambridge]]|years=1924\u20131930}}\n{{S-aft|after=[[Stanley Baldwin|The Earl Baldwin of Bewdley]]}}\n{{s-reg|uk}}\n{{s-new|creation}}\n{{s-ttl|title=[[Earl of Balfour]]|years=1922\u20131930}}\n{{s-aft|after=[[Gerald Balfour, 2nd Earl of Balfour|Gerald William Balfour]]}}\n{{s-ach}}\n{{s-bef|before=[[John Ringling]]}}\n{{s-ttl|title=[[List of covers of Time magazine (1920s)|Cover of ''Time'' Magazine]]\n|years=13 April 1925}}\n{{s-aft|after=[[Walter P. Chrysler]]}}\n{{s-ach|rec}}\n{{s-bef|before=[[Archibald Primrose, 5th Earl of Rosebery|The Earl of Rosebery]]}}\n{{s-ttl|title=[[Oldest living Prime Minister of the United Kingdom]]|years=1929\u20131930}}\n{{s-aft|after=[[David Lloyd George]]}}\n{{s-other|[[Scottish feudal lordship]]}}\n{{s-bef|before=[[Sir Charles Dalrymple, 1st Baronet|Sir Charles Dalrymple]]}}\n{{s-ttl|title=[[Lordship and Barony of Hailes|Lord and Baron of Hailes]]|years=1876\u20131930}}\n{{s-aft|after=[[Gerald Balfour, 2nd Earl of Balfour|Gerald William Balfour]]}}\n{{s-end}}\n\n{{Navboxes|title= Arthur Balfour navigational boxes|list=\n{{Prime Ministers of the United Kingdom}}\n{{Conservative Party (UK)}}\n{{Foreign Secretary}}\n{{Leader of the House of Commons}}\n{{Leaders of the Opposition UK}}\n{{Chancellors of the University of Cambridge}}\n{{Rectors of the University of St Andrews}}\n{{FBA 1902}}\n}}\n\n{{Authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Balfour, Arthur}}\n[[Category:1848 births]]\n[[Category:1930 deaths]]\n[[Category:20th-century Prime Ministers of the United Kingdom]]\n[[Category:First Lords of the Admiralty]]\n[[Category:People from East Lothian]]\n[[Category:People of the Victorian era]]\n[[Category:People educated at Eton College]]\n[[Category:Leaders of the Conservative Party (UK)]]\n[[Category:British Secretaries of State for Foreign Affairs]]\n[[Category:Secretaries for Scotland]]\n[[Category:Lord Presidents of the Council]]\n[[Category:Lords Privy Seal]]\n[[Category:Chancellors of the University of Cambridge]]\n[[Category:Chancellors of the University of Edinburgh]]\n[[Category:Rectors of the University of St Andrews]]\n[[Category:Rectors of the University of Glasgow]]\n[[Category:Conservative Party (UK) MPs for English constituencies]]\n[[Category:UK MPs 1874\u20131880]]\n[[Category:UK MPs 1880\u20131885]]\n[[Category:UK MPs 1885\u20131886]]\n[[Category:UK MPs 1886\u20131892]]\n[[Category:UK MPs 1892\u20131895]]\n[[Category:UK MPs 1895\u20131900]]\n[[Category:UK MPs 1900\u20131906]]\n[[Category:UK MPs 1906\u20131910]]\n[[Category:UK MPs 1910]]\n[[Category:UK MPs 1910\u20131918]]\n[[Category:UK MPs 1918\u20131922]]\n[[Category:Members of the Privy Council of Ireland]]\n[[Category:Members of the Privy Counc