populated places in the county be part of a municipality.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.sun-sentinel.com/news/fl-xpm-1985-06-16-8501230893-story.html|title=Broward's Annexation Drive Set to Begin|last=Hulse|first=Carl|date=June 16, 1985|work=South Florida Sun Sentinel|access-date=November 17, 2019}}</ref> Municipalities were often reluctant to annex neighborhoods which were not projected to yield enough tax revenue to cover the costs of providing services to those neighborhoods.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.sun-sentinel.com/news/fl-xpm-1985-11-13-8502200540-story.html|title=Unincorporated Areas Not an Easy Issue to Resolve|last=Jackson|first=David|date=November 13, 1985|work=South Florida Sun Sentinel|access-date=November 15, 2019}}</ref> In 2001 the Broward County Legislative Delegation adopted a policy encouraging the annexation of all unincorporated areas in Broward County into municipalities by October 1, 2005.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.fortlauderdale.gov/home/showdocument?id=11910|title=Broward Delegation Annexation Policy|last=|first=|date=August 2001|website=|access-date=November 17, 2019}}</ref> Formerly unincorporated neighborhoods that have been annexed into existing municipalities or combined to form new municipalities {{Asof|2018|lc=yes}} include:\n\n{|\n|-\n|valign=top|\n* [[Bonnie Loch-Woodsetter North, Florida|Bonnie Loch-Woodsetter North]] in Pompano Beach.\n* [[Broadview-Pompano Park, Florida|Broadview-Pompano Park]] in North Lauderdale.\n* [[Broward Estates, Florida|Broward Estates]] in Lauderhill.\n* [[Carver Ranches, Florida|Carver Ranches]] in West Park.\n* [[Chambers Estates, Florida|Chambers Estates]] in Dania Beach.\n* [[Chula Vista, Florida|Chula Vista Isles]] in Fort Lauderdale.\n* [[Collier Manor-Cresthaven, Florida|Collier Manor-Cresthaven]] in Pompano Beach.\n* [[Country Estates, Florida|Country Estates]] in Southwest Ranches.\n* [[Crystal Lake (Broward County, Florida)|Crystal Lake]] in Deerfield Beach.\n* [[Edgewater, Broward County, Florida|Edgewater]] in Dania Beach.\n* [[Estates of Fort Lauderdale, Florida|Estates of Fort Lauderdale]] in Dania Beach, and partially in Hollywood.\n* [[Godfrey Road, Florida|Godfrey Road]] in Parkland.\n|valign=top|\n* [[Golden Heights, Florida|Golden Heights]] in Fort Lauderdale.\n* [[Green Meadow, Florida|Green Meadow]] in Southwest Ranches.\n* [[Hacienda Village, Florida|Hacienda Village]] in Davie.\n* [[Ivanhoe Estates, Florida|Ivanhoe Estates]] in Southwest Ranches.\n* [[Kendall Green, Florida|Kendall Green]] in Pompano Beach.\n* [[Lake Forest, Florida|Lake Forest]] in West Park.\n* [[Leisureville, Florida|Leisureville]] in Pompano Beach.\n* [[Loch Lomond, Florida|Loch Lomond]] in Pompano Beach.\n|valign=top|\n* [[Melrose Park, Florida|Melrose Park]] in Fort Lauderdale.\n* [[Miami Gardens, Broward County, Florida|Miami Gardens]] in West Park.\n* [[North Andrews Gardens, Florida|North Andrews Gardens]] in Oakland Park.\n* [[Oak Point, Florida|Oak Point]] in Hollywood.\n* [[Palm Aire, Florida|Palm Aire]] in Fort Lauderdale.\n* [[Pine Island Ridge, Florida|Pine Island Ridge]] in Davie.\n* [[Pompano Beach Highlands, Florida|Pompano Beach Highlands]] in Pompano Beach.\n* [[Pompano Estates, Florida|Pompano Estates]] in Pompano Beach.\n* [[Ramblewood East, Florida|Ramblewood East]] in Coral Springs.\n|valign=top|\n* [[Ravenswood Estates, Florida|Ravenswood Estates]] in Dania Beach.\n* [[Riverland Village, Florida|Riverland Village]] in Fort Lauderdale.\n* [[Rock Island, Florida|Rock Island]] in Fort Lauderdale.\n* [[Rolling Oaks, Florida|Rolling Oaks]] in Southwest Ranches.\n* [[Royal Palm Ranches, Florida|Royal Palm Ranches]] in Cooper City.\n* [[St. George, Broward County, Florida|St. George]] in Lauderhill.\n* [[Sunshine Acres, Florida|Sunshine Acres]] in Davie.\n* [[Sunshine Ranches, Florida|Sunshine Ranches]] in Southwest Ranches.\n* [[Tedder, Florida|Tedder]] in Deerfield Beach.\n* [[Terra Mar, Florida|Terra Mar]] in Lauderdale-by-the-Sea, and partially in Pompano Beach.\n* [[Twin Lakes, Florida|Twin Lakes]] North of Prospect Road, in Fort Lauderdale. South of Prospect Road, in Oakland Park.\n* [[Utopia, Florida|Utopia]] in West Park.\n* [[Village Park, Florida|Village Park]] in North Lauderdale.\n* [[West Ken-Lark, Florida|West Ken-Lark]] in Lauderhill.\n|}\n\n=== Remaining unincorporated neighborhoods ===\nBy late in the first decade of the 21st century, annexation of remaining neighborhoods had stalled.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.sun-sentinel.com/news/fl-xpm-2007-10-21-0710200200-story.html|title=Annexation push leaves some behind|last=Ortega|first=Juan|date=October 21, 2007|work=South Florida Sun Sentinel|access-date=November 15, 2019}}</ref> {{Asof|2018}} the Broward County Municipal Services District serves seven unincorporated neighborhoods, including six [[census designated place]]s ([[Boulevard Gardens, Florida|Boulevard Gardens]], [[Broadview Park, Florida|Broadview Park]], [[Franklin Park, Florida|Franklin Park]], [[Hillsboro Pines, Florida|Hillsboro Pines]], [[Roosevelt Gardens, Florida|Roosevelt Gardens]] and [[Washington Park, Florida|Washington Park]]) and a parcel with a population of 72 in 2018, [[Hillsboro Ranches, Florida|Hillsboro Ranches]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.broward.org/MunicipalServicesDistrict/Pages/default.aspx|title=Broward Municipal Services District|last=|first=|date=2018|website=|access-date=November 17, 2019}}</ref> Other areas in the developed part of the county that are not in municipalities include the [[Hollywood Seminole Indian Reservation]], [[Fort Lauderdale-Hollywood International Airport]], several landfills and resource recovery facilities, and other scattered small parcels with few or no residents.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.broward.org/Planning/FormsPublications/Documents/BMSD2016.pdf|title=Municipal Services District|last=|first=|date=June 2016|website=Broward County|access-date=November 15, 2019}}</ref>\n\n==See also==\n* [[List of tallest buildings in Fort Lauderdale]]\n* [[National Register of Historic Places listings in Broward County, Florida|National Register of Historic Places listings in Broward County]], Florida\n* [[List of counties in Florida]]\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n{{Commons category|Broward County, Florida}}\n\n===Government links/Constitutional offices===\n* [https://web.archive.org/web/20090611140906/http://www.broward.org/ Broward County Government / Board of County Commissioners]\n* [http://www.browardsoe.org Broward County Supervisor of Elections]\n* [http://www.bcpa.net Broward County Property Appraiser]\n* [http://www.sheriff.org Broward County Sheriff's Office]\n\n====Special districts====\n* [http://www.browardschools.com Broward County Public Schools]\n* [http://www.browardhealth.org/ Broward Health (formerly North Broward Hospital District)]\n* [http://www.mhs.net/ South Broward Hospital District](Memorial Healthcare System)\n* [https://browardsoilandwater.org/ Broward Soil and Water Conservation District]\n* [http://www.sfwmd.gov South Florida Water Management District]\n\n====Judicial branch====\n* [http://www.browardclerk.org/ Broward County Clerk of Courts]\n* [http://www.clerk-17th-flcourts.org/ClerkWebsite/welcome2.aspx Broward County Clerk of Courts Records]\n* [http://www.browarddefender.org/ Broward County Public Defender]\n* [http://sao17.state.fl.us/ Broward State Attorney's Office, 17th Judicial Circuit]\n* [http://www.17th.flcourts.org/ Circuit and County Court for the 17th Judicial Circuit of Florida]\n\n===Tourism links===\n* [http://www.sunny.org Greater Fort Lauderdale Convention and Visitors Bureau]\n* [http://ufdc.ufl.edu/UF00072837 ''The Waterfront News''] local newspaper for Broward County, Florida fully and openly available in the [http://ufdc.ufl.edu/FDNL1 Florida Digital Newspaper Library]\n\n===Official sites===\n* [http://www.browardalliance.org/ The Broward Alliance] (Broward County's official public/private partnership for eco